# API Contract Rules (D-28)

## Invariants
- Public schemas in `app/schemas.py` — single source of truth
- `tests/contract/openapi.snapshot.json` is COMMITTED + auto-generated
- Any snapshot change REQUIRES a matching `app.version` bump (semver)
- CI `contract-check` diffs live OpenAPI vs snapshot → FAILS if diverged

## Breaking (major bump)
- Remove field, require new field, type change, rename endpoint/method

## Additive (minor bump)
- New optional field with default, new endpoint, new status code for NEW error

## Workflow
```
Edit app/schemas.py → python scripts/refresh_contract.py
  → if snapshot changed: bump app.version + commit together
```

## Forbidden
- Commit snapshot change without version bump (CI rejects)
- Hand-edit openapi.snapshot.json
- Breaking change without ADR when service has ≥ 1 consumer

See `.windsurf/rules/14-api-contracts.md`, AGENTS.md D-28.
